INSTALLATION :
- Unzip the package in your $SOFA_DIR/applications/plugins directory. 
- You should have the following layout for your directory tree:
  -$SOFA_DIR/
    -applications/
      -plugins/
        -ldidetection/

Now from your sofa root directory :

- Launch CMake a first time ('configure' in cmake-gui) then enable the option :
SOFA-PLUGIN_LDIDETECTION

- The default contact response is penalty-based. To use constraint-based response also, enable the following option in cmake :
SOFA-EXTERNAL_HAVE_EIGEN2

- configure again and then generate the project files, build the plugin and run
- From the GUI in the edit/PluginManager dialog add the libsofaldidetection.so (ldidetection_1_0.dll on Windows)
- Or from the commandline runSofa -l ../lib/sofa-plugins/libsofaldidetection.so (ldidetection_1_0.dll on Windows)
- You are ready to use the examples provided in the ldidetection/examples directory.

Note: qmake .pro project files are deprecated and should not be used anymore, please use CMake instead
